ve to all other cosmological model parameters,\nsource redshifts, magnification biases and so on. A knowledge of P(\\Delta\nt|\\theta) will also be useful in designing the observing program of future\nlarge scale synoptic variability surveys and for evaluating possible selection\nbiases operating against large splitting lens systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 5 Dec 2001 20:12:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
